snippet.textDisplay:
I feel like Blake settled for Gwen because he was depressed and insecure after his divorce, and he happened to be working with Gwen on The Voice so he just started dating her to cure his heartbreak.

It probably wasn't even that he wanted to date her in particular, as she is much older than he is, is from urban California, and already has children while Blake has none of his own...but he was probably so sad over his divorce from Miranda that he overlooked everything about Gwen that could have made their relationship not work in the long term.

She is likely too old to have any children with him, for example, even though he has expressed that he does want children, so he certainly did overlook that aspect when choosing to date her. Even if he didn't want to seem rude to reject her for this reason, it matters in the long run if having children is important to him.

Somehow I feel like a lot of men who are celebrities follow in Blake's footsteps and end up dating women who are not right for them or who will use them for money simply to cure depression, and then just figure it will work out on its own. It would be easy to let a woman into their lives and not concern themselves with expenses since they have so much else to worry about, but that still doesn't change the fact that they are being used on some level by women who may be gold diggers or who are not right for them. It's a pretty sad thing to witness.
snippet.textOriginal:
I feel like Blake settled for Gwen because he was depressed and insecure after his divorce, and he happened to be working with Gwen on The Voice so he just started dating her to cure his heartbreak. 

It probably wasn't even that he wanted to date her in particular, as she is much older than he is, is from urban California, and already has children while Blake has none of his own...but he was probably so sad over his divorce from Miranda that he overlooked everything about Gwen that could have made their relationship not work in the long term. 

She is likely too old to have any children with him, for example, even though he has expressed that he does want children, so he certainly did overlook that aspect when choosing to date her. Even if he didn't want to seem rude to reject her for this reason, it matters in the long run if having children is important to him.

 Somehow I feel like a lot of men who are celebrities follow in Blake's footsteps and end up dating women who are not right for them or who will use them for money simply to cure depression, and then just figure it will work out on its own. It would be easy to let a woman into their lives and not concern themselves with expenses since they have so much else to worry about, but that still doesn't change the fact that they are being used on some level by women who may be gold diggers or who are not right for them. It's a pretty sad thing to witness.
